reviews.review_text: Great vibe here. What an awesome time in the evolution of this band.  Cruddy recording overall.  But still an energized show.

My Bday Show My birthday show. Yep old timers, I was born on this day. Of course I had to see if there was a copy. Alas, they are all of pretty poor quality soundwise, but happy to see it here nonetheless.
Decent show from what I heard. If anyone has a cleaner copy please contact me.jlbxcx@hotmail

- The second set is a true diamond (in the rough due to the very grainy recording), one of the rare '72 shows that I actually like. Ironically, a bad '72 recording often tempers the harshness of their (I believe, and at the time) way-too-clean sound system. The first set is OK too, but the second really rips.
9/72 This is beginning of two weeks of great shows on the east coast.
First release of SBD from the Vault is playing today GD Channel on Sirius-XM.  Awesome sound quality FINALLY for this very very fine show
My 1st Dead Show I was 13 years old when i saw the dead
